1. HIGH – The v5 dual-run determinism checks still over-assert on `bundle.ticks`, so T2/T3 can fail even when the harness is correct. The plan now deep-equals `r1.bundle.ticks` vs `r2.bundle.ticks` in [2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-implementation-plan.md](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\docs\design\2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-implementation-plan.md:1217) and again in [2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-implementation-plan.md](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\docs\design\2026-04-27-synthetic-playtest-implementation-plan.md:1461). But a tick entry includes `metrics: WorldMetrics | null` in [src/session-bundle.ts](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\src\session-bundle.ts:56), and the recorder populates it from `this._world.getMetrics()` in [src/session-recorder.ts](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\src\session-recorder.ts:405). `World` defaults `instrumentationProfile` to `'full'` in [src/world.ts](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\src\world.ts:321), and `WorldMetrics` includes `durationMs` in [src/world.ts](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\src\world.ts:115), which is timing-backed via `performance.now()` in [src/world-internal.ts](C:\Users\38909\Documents\github\civ-engine\src\world-internal.ts:171). So whole-entry equality is comparing runtime timing noise, not just deterministic semantics. Fix: either normalize tick entries before comparison to `{ tick, diff, events, debug }`, or run the determinism worlds with `instrumentationProfile: 'release'` so recorded metrics are `null`.

The `CommandExecutionResult.sequence` issue is fixed by the whole-array execution comparison, but this metrics problem is still a real HIGH, so I would not ACCEPT v5 yet.
